                <h3>What is?</h3>
                <p>  
                    Pendap is a traditional Indonesian dish originating from the Minangkabau culture of West Sumatra. 
                    It is a flavorful beef dish cooked with a variety of spices, creating a rich and aromatic broth. 
                    The dish typically includes ingredients such as beef, coconut milk, turmeric, lemongrass, galangal, 
                    and kaffir lime leaves. The beef is simmered until tender in the fragrant coconut milk broth, absorbing 
                    the flavors of the spices. Pendap is known for its bold and complex flavors, making it a beloved dish in 
                    Indonesian cuisine, often served with steamed rice or as part of a larger spread of Minangkabau dishes.
                </p>
